The paper describes an implementation of Answer-set programming (ASP), which is a subfield of Artificial Intelligence (AI) that deals with knowledge representation and reasoning. The system is based on Datalog, which is a subfield of Databases (DB) that deals with deductive databases. The paper also mentions the use of Horn rules, which are a subfield of Logic (LO). Additionally, the paper discusses the syntax, use, and implementation of the system, which are topics related to Programming Languages (PL) and Software Engineering (SE).
